Azure Bootstrap
Linux Based Virtual Machines:

•	Ubuntu (14.04, 16.04 , 18.04)
•	RHEL (7.7 and above)
•	Cent OS (7.7 and above)
Use Bootstrap commands to deploy Applications in Virtual Machine:
•	Use bootstrap commands to deploy the applications like Apache, Tomcat, MySQL, and PostgreSQL while deploying the Virtual Machine. 
•	Copy and paste the bootstrap commands in cloud init while creating a VM in advances section. 
 
Commands to deploy applications in Ubuntu (14.04, 16.04, 18.04)
Apache:

# apt-get update
# apt-get install apache2 -y
# systemctl start apache2
Apache Tomcat:

# apt-get update
# apt-get install java
# apt-get install tomcat8 -y
# systemctl start tomcat8

MySQL:

# apt-get update
#apt-get install mysql –y
#systemctl start mysql

PostgreSQL:

# apt-get update
# apt-get –y install postgresql
# systemctl start postgresql






